Dia. 04 B is Correct Answer
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Was is too easy?
\par It seems White can block from both sides and he has no problem.
\par
\par However White's block at 1 (B) is the correct move. If he plays from the other side, he is going to be in trouble.
\par
\par After Black 2, White captures Black with 3.
\par
\par }
